rComments: Classes moved slowly and we just went through powerpoints on grammar and other english topics but prof Santor was engaging with the class and liked to talk a lot so it was still interesting. Tests relied heavily on class readings and fixing grammar problems. The only assignment was a final report but don't procrastinate as it can be long...

Overall this was a pretty easy class, even though English is my second language and my strong suit is definitely NOT writing. The class was not the most fun but the prof made it as bearable as she could. As a person shes the sweetest and super understanding. Just make sure you do the readings!

Professor Bar-On Santor is a truly amazing professor! She cares about her students and she is very accommodating. If you attend class and do the assigned readings you should have no problem getting a good grade in this class.

Professor Gefen is the sweetest, kindest, and most caring person you will ever meet. When you share your thoughts on something, she really listens. The tests are easy as long as you do your readings and pay attention in class. If you can, please take this course with her! She is always so accommodating and understanding of everyone's situation.

Not even gonna lie I went to like 2 classes the whole semester, read all of the lecture notes the morning of the tests, and did both report 1 and 2 in a few hours and still ended up with an A-, so needless to say this was the easiest class I've ever taken, as for Gefen she seemed like a good prof i think idk lol

This professor knows how to get the material across clearly. The tests were fair game if you read all the required readings prior to the test. Feedback on tests and the report paper were clear and fair. Take this prof, you won't regret it.

Professor Santor is a good professor. She is nice and even though the lectures can be boring, I actually learned a lot from them. It's most of the same stuff covered in high school but I actually understand how to apply it now. There is a lot of reading but it is doable. The tests are super easy. I studied the night before and got >90 on all 3.

She is honestly a real gem. So sweet and considerate and never gets irritated at students if they ask the same questions again. She's very patient and kind and the class is very straightforward. You'll learn a lot of writing skills that will help you your whole life! Solid elective choice 100% recommend.

Nice prof but doesn't always give clear instructions. PPT is over 100 slides (3-4 lectures in one PPT). Wouldn't want prof again bc of the length of the PPT. Had 3 quizzes and 4 writing assignments excluding the exam. You're only tested on what was taught in class. The course is open book. You're being graded on attendance.

Really nice prof and super accommodating. She offers late submissions w only 1% penalty each weekday. Her lecture notes are thorough and the tests are fairly simple since you can usually find the answers either in dgd or lecture notes. However, she sometimes runs out of time during class and has to cover things asynchronously

Professor Santor is great! Although lectures are heavy, she tried her best to do. For reports and tests, the feedback is detailed and helpful. During the pandemic, she understands the time zone difference that international students are facing. Just a reminder, for tests, be sure to read DGD PPTs, handouts, and selected readings from DGD handouts.
All the other teachers gave their students such good marks and this filler course somehow brought my average down. Useless

Professor Bar-On Santor is a great and caring professor. The course content is pretty boring but she tries her best. Review the topics discussed in class and read the readings and you'll do well on the tests. Start your report early and speak to your TA outside of class to know what they are expecting from you in your report.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: She is a very nice professor, and always ready to help her students. She is very easy to get in contact with outside of class through email, and very accommodating to her students especially with tech issues and covid-related struggles. Her grading is fair and her feedback is easy to understand. Really chill lectures and dgds too!! take her class !

Tests are open book (10 MC and 10 short answers) and very straightforward. Make sure you read the assigned readings for the tests. Grading is fair for the tests and the report. Lectures are mandatory (attendance grade) and you'll have to do one discussion starter during a lecture/DGD (participation grade) which is easy! Lectures were very chill.

She is an AMAZING person! So happy and class is judgement free. The class was overall minimal effort, to do well on tests you just have to take notes and read the course readings which can be done in a few hours. No exam just a final report. I learned so much about writing which I can actually see being very useful for the rest of my life.

Loved her. Especially with online classes rn, she is the most understanding and sweetest professors I have ever met! She cares about her student's mental health and is very easy to reach out to and chat with! Overall amazing teacher!

Gefen is extremely nice and accommodating. I actually learned a lot of material that has definitely improved my writing ability. She gives many different examples similar to her tests, which are pretty easy if you study. The required readings can be very long. She's a decent grader. Overall, the class is boring, but she's a good prof.

Great professor, and very kind. Always smiles and loves what she does. HOWEVER, her tests are beyond reason. She teaches to eliminate vagueness, ambiguity, redundancy, etc. but still manages to write her test questions with all these things. Ridiculous.
She is a dedicated and caring professor, she tries to make the lectures engaging. Be prepared to read A LOT.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Professor Gefen, you are truly a gem. One of the best profs I had first year. Hated English in H.S, and dreaded going to the first lecture, but I loved this class! Wasn't a huge fan of the lectures, but the report was really fun to write. I loved how comfortable she makes you feel when sharing your answers, with absolutely no judgement! 10/10 !!

The class reminded me of book club, we all showed up and got to talk about the text we were reading and our own personal experiences with the themes. She smiles when teaching literally the whole time and it is very evident she loves what she does. Is a very caring prof that wants to see you succeed.

Very boring class but there is nothing she can do about that. Do the readings and participate in the DGD and you'll get an easy A. Don't worry too much about paying attention in the lectures they're really just a third-grade grammar class. Start your report early and apply the feedback she gives to the first report. Good luck
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: The class is very easy. Show up, pay attention and start your report early and you're guaranteed an A. The tests are sort of hard because there is a lot of reading required. She's probably the hardest ENG prof but she's still pretty easy.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Caring']

rComments: SUPER BORING CLASS, the lectures were very dry and she made it difficult to want to come to class . Yet, she was a pretty easy marker on the papers and was really good about trying to get you as many marks as she can . Class was super easy just bring work from other classes to work on
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: I don like English class, but she was at least interesting some of the time, I did actually learn stuff in her class
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Lecture heavy', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: It's not hard, but attendance is basically required to know what's happening and to pass the class with good marks.

An absolute sweetheart. The class itself is easy IF YOU DO THE READINGS (Don't try to skim, that's how she gets you). My only complaint is that the readings themselves were very dull most of the time.
One of my favourite professors. She gets to know her students on a more personal level. Follow along during lectures and DGDs and you'll pass with flying colours!

This is probably the easiest course I've ever taken. Just show up to lectures to get the attendance marks and do other work in the back. The midterms are super easy as long as you do all the recommended readings. Is it also really easy to do well on the papers as long as you follow the criteria and talk to your TA.

Pretty good prof Extremely nice and always willing to help However there is a lot of content in her class you have to do to in order to do well but the content is no too bad just go to the dgds and READ THE SUGGESTED CONTENT BEFORE THE TEST some questions are very specific so a summary of the book wont cut it most of the time and youll be fine

I love her!!!!!!!!! She was always so understanding and caring. Took the time to know her students by name and is just the biggest sweetheart. I have only had one class with her, but wish I had taken more!!! She made the material accessible for all of her students.

Overall a really great professor. Her lectures can be very dull and boring but it's mostly because it's an English class. She truly cares about her students and makes sure that they all do the best they can in class. I learned a lot in the DGD's and if you can, take the DGD with Nick Slagter. He's one of the best TA's I've ever had.

She's really boring and I'm not sure if that's her fault or the course's fault but be ready for a snooze fest. There's an attendance mark so go to class, tests aren't that hard literally just reread powerpoints.

Gefen is a very nice and caring prof. However, she teaches a very dull course (ENG1112) so it's tough to stay engaged. The lectures feel very long but she does her best to try and be passionate about the material. Overall Gefen is a very good prof who teaches a course that it's hard to really care about.

For me I hate this class, but that's not her fault, its just the material. She is a very caring and well prepared prof, but sometimes her lectures got extremely boring. I heard shes one of the better teachers for this course.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Great professor. Normally I don't like English and dreaded having to take one as part of my degree but Gefen was such a good teacher that I enjoyed it. I legitimately improved my writing ability (which was horrendous before) and learned a lot from her class. Probably one of the best profs for this required course.

Well laid-out course; truly a kind, caring and genuine professor. (If you are not really interested in improving your language and are instead just looking to complete a mandatory course, perhaps she is not your best choice. Her session requires slightly more work than other sessions.)

She gave lots of feedback and support when writing reports. Make sure to attend the lectures frequently and always attend the DGD as they're essential to pass the midterms. Make sure to do the readings before the midterm and you'll be golden.

Her lectures are incredibly boring & uninspired, but the course is extremely easy so you really don't need to show up for class. Just read through the slides and you'll be covering the material in a much faster paced. I could go through each of her 1h 30min lectures  in 15 mins.

Please take her class for Technical report writing. You can easily get a good grade in her class. She has 3ish tests (not midterms) and 2 writing assignments. The second writing assignment is basically fixing all the errors you made in the first assignment and expanding on it.  And her DGDs aren't too bad either.

The readings and class in general are incredibly boring. Almost everything is straightforward and her tests are identical to the practice tests. Went to class every week and fell asleep every single time. Not sure why I went so often.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: We were "taught" in this class that criticism should be both constructive and correct, so: -The readings in the class were boring, pedantic and always based on the prof's anti-technology obsession. Please find some more diverse readings -The material should  be taught faster, with no  superfluous nagging to students about electronic distractions
Lectures are very boring but she is a kind prof, if you take her class MAKE SURE YOU DONT TAKE THE DGD WITH CORY SAMPSON he is the worst DGD instructor i have ever had.

We spend a lot of time talking about information that won't be on the exam, and yet examinations are long and specific. (We spent four classes on Frankenstein and did not even reach the part where The Monster is created before the semester ended)
Her class is hard for students who use English as the second language.

I really enjoyed this prof! I did find that sometimes she was a little repetitive, but she was very helpful with the assignments and showed that she cared about her students. Would take her class again!

Once you get past the accent and misuse of words she is such a nice lady who truly wants you to do well in the course. Posts all her lecture slides online. DGDs are a must since all tests are done then. You can tell she loves her job.

Professor Bar-On Santor really encouraged me to pursue my studies in English Literature. She knows her stuff, and by the end of the class you'll know it just as well. She gives in-depth summaryanalysis, line per line, and everything she says ends up on the midtermfinal. If you listen, do the readings, and retain what she says, it's an easy A!

The prof was very forward about expectations and teaches the course as best as she can. The course itself is really boring and besides the fact that it is compulsory for Engineering students, its a complete waste of time.

Her lectures are long, boring, and her voice drags on and on. The content of the course itself is extremely dry, making it difficult to attend class. The TA's mark extremely hard and the DGD's are super boring. She has very strict views (hates technology etc..) and she will yell at you if you talk during class.  Avoid if you can!!!!!

PLs avoid her class because you will be writing the stupid report since the beginning of the semester.  Compare to another sections, this is not an "easy to pass one". When going to her lectures, you won t get anything except sentence corrections(boring). The TAs are hard markers. My worst class ever.

Lectures are not worth going to. This course teaches you how to write sentences, something a 10 year old child in elementary school can do. She is against technology. DGDs are boring. This course fails miserably to educate you in writing and is a complete waste of time. If you value your life DO NOT TAKE THIS COURSE.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'So many papers']

rComments: She speaks to her students, and she provides fantastic feedback on midterms which allows you to learn where you went wrong and improve drastically.
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Get ready to read', 'Amazing lectures ']

rComments: Basically if you want to do well you have to agree with her perspective. Regardless of how obscure her connections or observations are between the books, Use them. Or fail, your choice

Excellent prof. Clearly defines what is expected for you to know from each novel, as well as encourages you to participate in class discussions and provides you with positive feedback with an unique idea. Tough marker, but if you follow her requirements, you should be fine
AVOID AVOID AVOID. Do not take this class. It will make you entirely miserable and the essays are brutal- brutal to write and brutally marked. She speaks about 2 words/hr, too.

WARNING: If you want to get a good grade, you need to put your own opinions aside. Even if you are right. She is against technology, internet, and the change in literature. Don't try to be a good writer by talking about both sides of an argument during an essay. Only talk about her side.
